# Deploy to Device After Every Change

After making any code change to the project, you MUST build and install the app on the connected iPhone using `xcodebuild`. Do not consider a task complete until the build succeeds and the app is running on device.

## Build & Deploy Commands

**Step 1 — Build:**
```bash
xcodebuild \
  -project ChoresApp.xcodeproj \
  -scheme ChoresApp \
  -destination 'id=B69F2F50-46C4-55A2-B259-F1FA98FBF817' \
  -configuration Debug \
  build \
  CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=YES \
  2>&1 | tail -20
```

**Step 2 — Install on device:**
```bash
xcrun devicectl device install app \
  --device B69F2F50-46C4-55A2-B259-F1FA98FBF817 \
  /Users/simeonrubin/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/ChoresApp-cxffvpxauigyvzaqawqntuvowfkm/Build/Products/Debug-iphoneos/ChoresApp.app
```

- Device: **Simeon's iPhone 15 Pro** (`B69F2F50-46C4-55A2-B259-F1FA98FBF817`)
- Project: `ChoresApp.xcodeproj`
- Scheme: `ChoresApp`

## Rules

- Run the build command after **every** set of code changes, before finishing your turn.
- If the build fails, fix the errors and rebuild until it succeeds.
- Report the build result (success or errors) to the user.
